    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "15% isn't that big of a drop, we can live with that. The main issue is the legal stuff—the \"predictive\" part of the system has been flagging too many people in certain neighborhoods who end up not being a threat, and it's causing some serious racial profiling concerns. We just need to get back to basics: if something moves, the alarm goes off. No more \"predicting\" intent or analyzing demographic patterns. Why exactly would the predictive model be so much better than just simple motion sensors?",
